Persistence of increased cardiovascular risk in patients with Cushing's disease after five years of successful cure. Patients with Cushing's disease (CD) mainly die because of cardiovascular accidents. The aim of this study was to evaluate whether patients with CD still have increased cardiovascular risk and suffer from premature atherosclerosis once cured. Fifteen patients cured from CD for a long term period (5 yr), 30 sex-and age-matched controls, and 30 body mass index (BMI)-matched controls were included in this study. BMI waist to hip ratio (WHR)